-->\n\n==Semi-finals==\n<section begin=SF />\nThe draw for the semi-finals, originally scheduled for 20 March 2020 (after the quarter-final draw), was postponed.<ref name=\"week postponed\"/><ref name=\"QF_SF_F_draw\"/><section end=SF />\n<!--\n===Summary===\n<section begin=SF />\nThe first legs will be played on , and the second legs will be played on  2020.\n\n{{TwoLegStart}}\n{{TwoLegResult|||1|||[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Matches 3|{{small|28/29 Apr}}]]|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Matches 3|{{small|5/6 May}}]]}}\n{{TwoLegResult|||2|||[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Matches 3|{{small|28/29 Apr}}]]|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Matches 3|{{small|5/6 May}}]]}}\n|}<section end=SF />\n\n===Matches===\n{{Football box\n|id         =\n|date       = 28/29 {{Start date|2020|4||df=y}}\n|time       = 21:00\n|team1      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|score      =\n|team2      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    =\n|attendance =\n|referee    =\n|report     =\n}}\n{{Football box\n|id         =\n|date       = 5/6 {{Start date|2020|5||df=y}}\n|time       = 21:00\n|team1      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|score      =\n|team2      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    =\n|attendance =\n|referee    =\n|report     =\n}}\n----\n{{Football box\n|id         =\n|date       = 28/29 {{Start date|2020|4||df=y}}\n|time       = 21:00\n|team1      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|score      =\n|team2      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    =\n|attendance =\n|referee    =\n|report     =\n}}\n{{Football box\n|id         =\n|date       = 5/6 {{Start date|2020|5||df=y}}\n|time       = 21:00\n|team1      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|score      =\n|team2      = {{fbaicon|}}\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    =\n|attendance =\n|referee    =\n|report     =\n}}-->\n\n==Final==\n<section begin=F />\n{{main|2020 UEFA Champions League Final}}\n\nThe final is scheduled to be played at the [[Atat\u00fcrk Olympic Stadium]] in [[Istanbul]]. The \"home\" team (for administrative purposes) will be determined by an additional draw held after the quarter-final and semi-final draws.<ref name=\"QF_SF_F_draw\"/>\n{{:2020 UEFA Champions League Final}}<section end=F />\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Uefa Champions League Knockout Phase 2019-20}}\n[[Category:2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|*3]]\n[[Category:February 2020 sports events in Europe]]\n[[Category:March 2020 sports events in Europe]]\n<!--[[Category: 2020 sports events in Europe]]\n[[Category: 2020 sports events in Europe]]-->\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "The '''2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase''' began on 18 February 2020 with the round of 16 and will end with the [[2020 UEFA Champions League Final|final]] at the [[Atat\u00fcrk Olympic Stadium]] in [[Istanbul]], Turkey, to decide the champions of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League]].<ref name=\"calendar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2589462.html|title=2019/20 Champions League match and draw calendar|publisher=UEFA.com|date=14 January 2019}}</ref> A total of 16 teams compete in the knockout phase.<ref name=\"regulations\">{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/60/37/12/2603712_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=Regulations of the UEFA Champions League 2019/20|publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref>\n\nTimes are [[Central European Time|CET]]/[[Central European Summer Time|CEST]],{{refn|group=note|[[Central European Time|CET]] ([[UTC+01:00|UTC+1]]) for dates up to 28 March 2020 (round of 16), and [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00|UTC+2]]) for dates thereafter (quarter-finals, semi-finals and final).}} as listed by UEFA (local times, if different, are in parentheses).\n\n==Qualified teams==\nThe knockout phase involves the 16 teams which qualified as winners and runners-up of each of the eight groups in the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Group\n!width=210|Winners<br />(seeded in round of 16 draw)\n!width=210|Runners-up<br />(unseeded in round of 16 draw)\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group A|A]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|FRA}} [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group B|B]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|GER}} [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ENG}} [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group C|C]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|ENG}} [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ITA}} [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group D|D]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|ITA}} [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ESP}} [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group E|E]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|ENG}} [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ITA}} [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group F|F]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|ESP}} [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|GER}} [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group G|G]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|GER}} [[RB Leipzig]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|FRA}} [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]\n|-\n![[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group H|H]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3BB|{{fbaicon|ESP}} [[Valencia CF|Valencia]]\n|bgcolor=#BBF3FF|{{fbaicon|ENG}} [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|}\n\n==Format==\nEach tie in the [[Single-elimination tournament|knockout phase]], apart from the final, is played over [[Two-legged tie|two legs]], with each team playing one leg at home. The team that scores more goals on aggregate over the two legs advances to the next round. If the aggregate score is level, the [[away goals rule]] is applied, i.e. the team that scores more goals away from home over the two legs advances. If away goals are also equal, then [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] is played. The away goals rule is again applied after extra time, i.e. if there are goals scored during extra time and the aggregate score is still level, the visiting team advances by virtue of more away goals scored. If no goals are scored during extra time, the winners are decided by a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]]. In the final, which is played as a single match, if the score is level at the end of normal time, extra time is played, followed by a penalty shoot-out if the score is still level.<ref name=\"regulations\"/>\n<section begin=Format />\nThe mechanism of the draws for each round is as follows:\n*In the draw for the round of 16, the eight group winners are seeded, and the eight group runners-up are unseeded. The seeded teams are drawn against the unseeded teams, with the seeded teams hosting the second leg. Teams from the same group or the same association cannot be drawn against each other.\n*In the draws for the quarter-finals and semi-finals, there are no seedings, and teams from the same group or the same association can be drawn against each other. As the draws for the quarter-finals and semi-finals are held together before the quarter-finals are played, the identity of the quarter-final winners is not known at the time of the semi-final draw. A draw is also held to determine which semi-final winner is designated as the \"home\" team for the final (for administrative purposes as it is played at a neutral venue).<section end=Format />\n\nFor the quarter-finals and semi-finals, teams from the same city are not scheduled to play at home on the same day or on consecutive days, due to logistics and crowd control.<ref>{{cite web |title=Why Manchester United's UEFA Champions League home leg vs Barcelona has been reversed |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-united-champions-league-draw-15972728 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=15 March 2019 |accessdate=15 March 2019}}</ref> To avoid such scheduling conflict, if the two teams are drawn to play at home for the same leg, the order of legs of the tie involving the team with the lower domestic ranking in the qualifying season is reversed from the original draw.<ref>{{cite web |title=Champions League quarter-final and semi-final draws: all you need to know |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2589810.html |work=UEFA |date=13 March 2019 |accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\nThe schedule is as follows (all draws are held at the UEFA headquarters in [[Nyon]], Switzerland).<ref name=\"calendar\"/>\n\nFollowing the first set of round of 16 second leg matches, the competition was postponed indefinitely due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]].<ref name=\"week postponed\">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/news/newsid=2641054.html |title=All of this week's UEFA matches postponed |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=15 March 2020 |access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"suspended\">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/mediaservices/mediareleases/newsid=2641071.html |title=UEFA postpones EURO 2020 by 12 months |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> The final, originally scheduled to take place on 30 May 2020, was officially postponed on 23 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/mediaservices/mediareleases/newsid=2641114.html |title=UEFA Club Finals postponed |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> A working group was set up by UEFA to decide the calendar of the remainder of the season.<ref name=\"working group\">{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/insideuefa/news/newsid=2641077.html |title=Resolution of the European football family on a coordinated response to the impact of the COVID-19 on competitions |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Round\n!Draw date\n!First leg\n!Second leg\n|-\n|Round of 16\n|16 December 2019, 12:00\n|18\u201319 & 25\u201326 February 2020\n|10\u201311 March & TBD 2020{{efn|Second week of matches originally scheduled for 17\u201318 March 2020}}\n|-\n|Quarter-finals{{efn|Quarter-final first legs originally scheduled for 7\u20138 April, and second legs 14\u201315 April 2020}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|TBD{{efn|Quarter-final, semi-final and final draws originally scheduled for 20 March 2020, 12:00}}\n|TBD\n|TBD\n|-\n|Semi-finals{{efn|Semi-final first legs originally scheduled for 28\u201329 April, and second legs 5\u20136 May 2020}}\n|TBD\n|TBD\n|-\n|Final\n|colspan=\"2\"|TBD at [[Atat\u00fcrk Olympic Stadium]], [[Istanbul]]{{efn|Final originally scheduled for 30 May 2020}}\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Round of 16==\n<section begin=R16 />\nThe draw for the round of 16 was held on 16 December 2019, 12:00 [[Central European Time|CET]].<ref name=\"R16_draw\">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/draws/2020/2001141/ |title=UEFA Champions League round of 16 draw |publisher=UEFA.com}}</ref><section end=R16 />\n\n===Summary===\n<section begin=R16 />\nThe first legs were played as scheduled on 18, 19, 25 and 26 February, as were the first set of second legs on 10 and 11 March 2020. Due to concerns over the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]], the second set of second leg matches were postponed indefinitely by UEFA on 13 March 2020.<ref name=\"week postponed\"/>\n\nThe first leg of the Atalanta v Valencia tie was retrospectively blamed by local civic and medical authorities for contributing to the extremely high concentration of coronavirus cases in Atalanta's home city of [[Bergamo]]. Several fans and players of Valencia also had positive diagnoses after returning from the game.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Azzoni |first1=Tales |last2=Dampf |first2=Andrew |title=Game Zero: Spread of virus linked to Champions League match |url=https://apnews.com/ae59cfc0641fc63afd09182bb832ebe2 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |publisher=Associated Press |date=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bacon |first1=Jake |title=Atalanta vs Valencia Champions League clash was a 'biological bomb' and 'infected 40,000 fans' with coronavirus, claims Bergamo mayor |url=https://talksport.com/football/687311/atalanta-valencia-champions-coronavirus-bergamo-mayor/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |publisher=Talksport |date=25 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giuffrida |first1=Angela |title=Bergamo mayor says football match escalated infections in Italian province |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/24/bergamo-mayor-says-football-match-escalated-coronavirus-infections-italian-province |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{TwoLegStart}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Borussia Dortmund]]|GER|2\u20133|'''[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]'''|FRA|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Borussia Dortmund v Paris Saint-Germain|2\u20131]]|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Paris Saint-Germain v Borussia Dortmund|0\u20132]]}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]|ESP|2|[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]|ENG|[[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Real Madrid v Manchester City|1\u20132]]|[[